conditionStatement.statementValue:
The Approval Holder shall not conduct maintenance except for the following:

(a) restoration maintenance to design grades as indicated in the plans submitted with the application;

(b) removal of debris and vegetation;

(c) repair/replacement of culverts;

(d) repair of seepage control system; and

(e) any other maintenance actions authorized in writing by the Director.

To reduce fragmentation and integrate land development, the disposition holder shall locate drilling, remote sumps or production facilities as follows;

(a)  Use unoccupied, existing disturbances that are within 250 metres of the proposed disposition boundary,  regardless of quarter or section lines, or;

(b)  Adjoin to existing occupied dispositions and/or existing linear disturbances that are within 250 metres of the proposed disposition boundary, regardless of quarter or section lines, or;

(c)  Where multiple existing occupied dispositions or existing linear disturbances exist, the activity must adjoin to the maximum number of dispositions and disturbances that align with the activity.

When requested by the Director, the Approval Holder shall record and retain for each calendar year the following information and shall provide this information to the Director on or before January 31 of each year:

(a) monthly readings of the number of cubic meters of water pumped from the drainage site(s) including dates and times the readings were taken;

(b) monthly measurements of water levels from the drainage site(s) including dates and times at which readings were taken;

(c) total annual quantity of water pumped expressed in cubic metres;

(d) annual submissions of chemical analysis;

(e) a review of the performance of the drainage site(s) during the past year and an assessment, supported by graphs and calculations, of the performance of the aquifer;

(f) recommendations for adjustments of pumping rates, the number and location of observation wells, and drainage site(s) monitoring requirements;

(g) a report prepared by a qualified groundwater consultant on the aquifer performance and recommendations for amendments to the approval;

and any other information requested by the Director.

The Siltation and Erosion Control Plan shall specify measures to minimize and avoid siltation and erosion of the water body and shall include, at a minimum, the following information:

(a) measures to ensure no removal or disturbance of bank vegetation outside the site of the activity;

(b) site preparation practices to be used on erodible soils;

(c) measures for the management of surface and subsurface water flow to minimize siltation and erosion of any water body;

(d) measures for the stabilization of all disturbed areas until vegetation or other long-term erosion control methods are fully established and functioning; and

(e) measures for the management of excavated material.
